User Submitted


          
          
            Field Trip: U.S. Geothermal Plant at Neal Hot Springs 
          
      
        

When:  Sat., July 22, 7 a.m.-6 p.m.

Phone: 208-853-1678

Email: contact.us@idahomuseum.org

Price: $10-$15


 Odds & Ends, Events & Workshops, User Submitted
 


           
                   
          Join Roy Mink for a field trip to the plant, located west of Vale, Ore. Because it’s an active industrial site, sturdy hiking boots and full-length pants are required (no T-shirts). The noise level will be high, so earplugs are provided. Take lunch and water. Meet at the WinCo parking lot on Meridian Road at I-84 at 7:30 a.m. for a prompt departure at 8 a.m. Return to Boise by 6 p.m. Visit idahomuseum.org for critical details about the trip. Sponsored by the Idaho Museum of Mining and Geology. Call Steve at 208-853-1678 to preregister. 
  
          
        






Idaho Museum of Mining and Geology



2455 Old Penitentiary Road, Boise
East Boise
ID
83712


43.60291;-116.16206


 208-368-9876


idahomuseum.org






