US Geothermal stock analysis involves checking at least a few of the important things like: Revenue: The money received by selling of goods or services comes under this line item.  A YoY growth (See: US Geothermal revenue chart) implies that the company is growing, which has been the case with US Geothermal.  One must stay away from stocks whose revenues are declining.  Bottom line: The word bottom line comes because it is usually the last line of the income statement and refers to the actual profits after deducting all expenses from the revenues.  HTM stock had a healthy bottom line growth.  The income statement is also called statement of revenue and expense.  The financials along with US Geothermal historical stock prices provides a lot of details about the firm.  . 

