Warranty


Warranty is through manufacture only. Please read manufactures warranty carefully as certain manufactures have stipulations in their warranties concerning internet sales or diy sales. Equipment is intended for installation by trained Professionals. Disclaimer and Return Policy - [For ALL Orders] Please read before ordering Disclaimer Of Liability for Ordering and Installing Parts Geothermal Products suggests having all parts, accessories and equipment installed by a qualified heating and air conditioning technician. All manufactures have rights to reject warranty claims if not professionally installed. If a customer attempts to install any part, accessory or equipment, he or she should have a thorough understanding of electricity, natural gas, propane and how to work with aforementioned, reading wiring diagrams and a general knowledge of the work to be performed. Power should always be turned off and verified with a volt meter before replacing any part. In no way shall Geothermal Products be liable for any warranty claims, loss, damage, fire, explosion, injury, including any incidental or consequential damages, or death as a result of ordering and/or installing any parts from our website or from the results of any action taken due to reading information found on our website. All information provided on this Web site is subject to change without notice. While efforts have been made to make this Web site helpful and accurate, due to the open nature of this Web site, and the potential for errors in the storage and transmission of digital information, Geothermal Products does not warrant the accuracy of information obtained from this Web site. Geothermal Products is a full line distributor for all of your geothermal product needs. Please call 877-220-0221.






































